The paper deals with the development and validation of automatic techniques to detect cephalometric landmarks from digital images of frontal faces in the forensic field. This involves the use of computer vision and image processing techniques within a supervised learning procedure. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, since the paper also involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and machine learning (ML) techniques, it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper involves the use of information retrieval (IR) techniques to detect landmarks, it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and since it involves multimedia (MM) data (digital images), it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
